description:
&lt;p&gt;A fantastic opportunity has arisen for a highly motivated and enthusiastic Band 7 Community Specialist Practitioner to join our Care at Home Frailty Team in the Erewash locality, based in Long Eaton.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Care at Home Frailty Team supports patients either at home or within a Care Home setting as their health deteriorates, therefore preventing avoidable admissions, championing advance care planning and in partnership with the patient; supporting long term disease management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This service identifies and focuses on the frailest patients in Erewash and works with the wider community services team to support these patients to remain within their usual place of residence, or within their Care Home environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Team comprises of Advanced Nurse/Clinical Practitioners, Community Nurse Practitioners a Community General Practitioner, Community Registered Nurses, support staff and Care Coordinators who work closely with other health and social care professionals across primary and secondary care, as well as with patients, families and carers in both a home and care home setting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successful candidates will need to hold the Non-Medical Prescribing and Clinical Decisions Modules or will be employed on a Band 6 trainee basis whilst being supported to complete these qualifications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Louise Shipley, Team Lead&lt;/p&gt;
